raw_meta_yaml:
{% set name = "SOAPpy" %}
{% set version = "0.12.22" %}
{% set sha256 = "e70845906bb625144ae6a8df4534d66d84431ff8e21835d7b401ec6d8eb447a5" %}

package:
  name: {{ name|lower }}
  version: {{ version }}

source:
  fn: {{ name }}-{{ version }}.zip
  url: https://pypi.io/packages/source/{{ name[0] }}/{{ name }}/{{ name }}-{{ version }}.zip
  sha256: {{ sha256 }}

build:
  number: 1000
  skip: True  # [ not py2k or win ]
  script: python setup.py install --single-version-externally-managed --record record.txt

requirements:
  build:
    - python
    - setuptools
  run:
    - python
    - wstools
    - defusedxml

test:
  imports:
    - SOAPpy
    - SOAPpy.Client
    - SOAPpy.Config
    - SOAPpy.Errors
    - SOAPpy.NS
    - SOAPpy.Parser
    - SOAPpy.Server
    - SOAPpy.SOAPBuilder
    - SOAPpy.SOAP
    - SOAPpy.Types
    - SOAPpy.URLopener
    - SOAPpy.Utilities
    - SOAPpy.version
    - SOAPpy.WSDL

about:
  home: https://github.com/kiorky/SOAPpy
  license: BSD-3-Clause
  license_family: BSD
  license_file: '{{ RECIPE_DIR }}/LICENSE'
  summary: 'Simple to use SOAP library for Python'

  description: |
    Disclaimer (from upstream package)
    ==================================
    Please use `suds <https://pypi.python.org/pypi/suds>`_ rather than SOAPpy.
    SOAPpy is old and clamsy.
  dev_url: https://github.com/kiorky/SOAPpy

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - pvanheus
    - AjitPS
